Merge pull request #2 from aartemiev/master

Change the channel limit description in README.md
support bsdmake out of the box
bash is non-standard on BSD platforms
Do not settle on yacc; bison or byacc preferred
fix compile error with fbsd yacc
fix code on platform that does not support atomic intrinsics
disregard message boundary when --channel-bandwidth is specified
draw clock only if terminal is utf-8 aware

fix for spurious writeability

Sometimes libev gives us WRITE notification even after we reconfigure
the watcher to remove the WRITE interest. This patch fixes the
timer work so it becomes immune to these spurious events.
fixed comment nesting // compiled with newer (more strict) compiler
Add WebSocket masking on client->server communication (mandated by RFC).
do not aggregate latency histograms from data sink connections (-l)
function order fix for older compiler
more cross-platform support for atomic math
dependency from system libraries is ok
make check will fail in travis due to network socket restrictions
int rc moved up so it is not accidently lost in ifdefs
